
# Engagement Recovery & Channel Customization

Fixing broken community features (Subscriptions/Comments) and empowering creators with professional channel branding (Banners/Avatars).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Migration**: I will be unifying the `subscriptions` and `comments` tables to ensure RLS (Row Level Security) allows for seamless organic growth.
>
> **Storage Buckets**: I will be creating (or ensuring existence of) `avatars` and `banners` storage buckets for creator uploads. Creators will need to be logged in to customize their vibe.

## Proposed Changes

### Database & Security
#### [NEW] [engagement-migration.sql](file:///C:/GOLive/scripts/engagement-migration.sql)
- **Unify Subscriptions**: Ensure standard `subscriber_id`/`channel_id` composite key and global RLS access.
- **Profiles Expansion**: Add `banner_url`, `channel_color`, and `follower_count` to the `profiles` table.
- **Comments Resilience**: Ensure the `comments` table has proper foreign keys and non-restrictive RLS for authenticated users.

### Creator Studio
#### [MODIFY] [SettingsPage](file:///C:/GOLive/app/studio/settings/page.tsx)
- **Image Uploaders**: Implement professional drag-and-drop uploaders for both Avatar and Banner.
- **Supabase Storage Integration**: Connect uploaders to the Storage API with automatic resizing/compression placeholders.
- **Real-time Preview**: Show the new banner/avatar instantly before saving.

### Engagement Components
#### [MODIFY] [SubscribeButton.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/SubscribeButton.tsx)
- Fix the `onToggle` callback to ensure the parent UI (Watch/Profile) syncs instantly without page refreshes.
- Ensure the button state persists correctly across all views.

#### [MODIFY] [CommentSection.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/CommentSection.tsx)
- Ensure the realtime channel is correctly scoped to the `video_id`.
- Add "Stay" persistence: Verify that local state updates are correctly driven by DB events.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Subagent Tests
- **Subscription Test**: Subscribe to a creator and verify the "Subscribed" state remains after a page reload.
- **Comment Test**: Post a comment and verify it appears instantly and persists after navigation.
- **Upload Test**: Upload a banner in Settings and verify it appears on the public Profile page.

### Manual Verification
- Verify that users cannot subscribe to themselves (already handled in code, but worth verifying).
- Test the "Hype" and "Like" buttons to ensure they also persist.
